parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the floor pan can cause holes to form, allowing exhaust fumes to enter the vehicle, and potentially leading to carbon monoxide poisoning. Additionally, the rust can weaken the structural integrity of the vehicle, making it more susceptible to accidents.
symptoms: rusting or corrosion of the floor pan
and wind rushing through the floor while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft/camshaft position sensor can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the engine to run rough, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing an accident. It can also cause the vehicle to fail emissions tests.

the engine makes an abnormal noise
and the vehicle has difficulty starting.

and the check engine warning light illuminates.
